9/6/22, 4:02â€¯PM - Suzal Kachhadiya: #include<iostream>
using namespace std;

bool possibleSol(int arr[],int n,int k,int mid){
    int boardsum=0,painters=1;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if((boardsum+arr[i])<=mid){
            boardsum+=arr[i];
            }
            else{
                painters++;
                if(painters>k || arr[i]>mid){
                    return false;
                }
                boardsum=arr[i];
            }    
        }
        return true;
}

int main(){
        int n,k;
        cin>>n>>k;
        int arr[n],sum=0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            cin>>arr[i];
            sum+=arr[i];
        }
        int ans=-1;
        int s=0,e=sum,mid=s+(e-s)/2;
        while(s<=e){
            if(possibleSol(arr,n,k,mid)){
            ans=mid;
            e=mid-1;
            }
            else{
                s=mid+1; 
            }
            mid=s+(e-s)/2;
        }    
         cout<<ans<<endl;
return 0;
}

	["07"]="Computer Engineering"

5/29/23, 10:38â€¯AM - Nikunj Navadiya: import javafx.application.Application;
import javafx.event.EventHandler;
import javafx.scene.Scene;
import javafx.scene.input.KeyCode;
import javafx.scene.input.KeyEvent;
import javafx.scene.layout.Pane;
import javafx.scene.paint.Color;
import javafx.scene.shape.Circle;
import javafx.stage.Stage;
public class App4 extends Application{
public static void main(String args[])
{
launch(args);
}
@Override
public void start(Stage primaryStage) throws Exception{
Circle c1 = new Circle(20);
c1.setFill(Color.RED);
Pane p = new Pane();
c1.setTranslateX(0);
p.getChildren().add(c1);
// Keyboard k = new Keyboard();
c1.setOnKeyPressed(new EventHandler<KeyEvent>() {
@Override
public void handle(KeyEvent event) {
if(event.getCode() == KeyCode.UP && c1.getTranslateY()>20)
{
c1.setTranslateY(c1.getTranslateY()-10);
}
if(event.getCode() == KeyCode.DOWN && c1.getTranslateY()<(p.getHeight()-20))
{
c1.setTranslateY(c1.getTranslateY()+10);
Practical-9 2
}
if(event.getCode() == KeyCode.LEFT && c1.getTranslateX()>20)
{
c1.setTranslateX(c1.getTranslateX()-10);
}
if(event.getCode() == KeyCode.RIGHT && c1.getTranslateX()<(p.getWidth()-20))
{
c1.setTranslateX(c1.getTranslateX()+10);
}
}
});
primaryStage.setScene(new Scene(p,600,600));
primaryStage.show();
c1.requestFocus();
}
}

Greetings of the day!

In our continuous effort to keep you safeguarded from the market related frauds and increase awareness while conducting trades, we request you to go through an order passed by SEBI dated June 14,2023 against below entity/individuals in the matter of unregistered investment advisory activities and would request you to ensure that you do not engage with these entity/individuals:
Kabir Financial Services Pvt. Ltd. - AAICK9402B
Sayyed Shujauddin - CZIPS9418M
Farhat Perween - CUTPP6462J
Above entity/individuals were unregistered Investment Advisors. Telegram channels operated by these entity/individuals are advertising and offering various securities market packages for providing calls / tips / securities related advise. In return for the said calls / tips / advise being given, fee is being collected from subscribers of various packages in personal bank accounts. They have guaranteed assured profits to the many subscribers of their Telegram chats which is nothing more than a ploy to lure and induce investors to deal in securities by availing unregistered investment advisory services.

List of Telegram Channels operated by above entity/individuals:
https://t.me/kabir_banknifty
https://t.me/kabir_banknifty_options
https://t.me/masterkabir_banknifty
https://t.me/nifty_banknifty_options_Kabir
https://t.me/kabir_nifty_banknifty

The investors are cautioned and advised not to subscribe to any such scheme/ product offered by any person/entity offering indicative/assured/guaranteed returns in the stock market as the same is prohibited by law. Further, investors are advised not to share their trading credentials such as user id/ password with anyone.

Participation in such prohibited schemes is at investors' own risk, cost and consequences. Accordingly, we would request you to be cautious and ensure that you do not engage in any activities with such persons/entities.

In addition to above, we also expect the investors to refer below guidelines while dealing in the securities market.
Clients/investors are cautioned to abstain from dealing in any schemes of unauthorized collective investments/portfolio management, indicative/guaranteed/fixed returns/payments etc.
Do not deal with an unregistered stockbroker/Authorised person.
Do not fall prey to fixed/guaranteed returns schemes.
Please do not transfer funds, for the purposes of trading to anyone, including an authorized person or an associate of the broker, other than a SEBI-registered Stockbroker.
Do not fall prey to fraudsters sending emails and SMSs luring to trade in stocks/securities promising huge profits.
Do not share your login credentials including OTP/PIN with any third party.
Do not follow herd mentality for investments. Seek expert and professional advice for your investments.
Assuring service True to You, Always.
Team Angel One

8/8/23, 1:50â€¯PM - Kenil Kanani: Here is a summary of the Tata Code of Conduct using simple language:

- Treat people fairly and with respect. Do not discriminate.  

- Be honest and transparent. Do not bribe.

- Make good and safe products that follow rules. Be fair in selling and competing.  

- Protect the environment and community. Reduce impact and help society.

- Choose suppliers fairly. Require them to be ethical too. Respect others' property.

- Give shareholders correct and timely information. Keep proper records.

- Work constructively with government. Do not improperly influence elections or policies.  

- Cooperate with Tata companies. Resolve disputes peacefully.  

- Speak up about ethics concerns without fear. 

- Follow the Code. Face action if you violate it.

- The Code promotes ethical actions, good corporate citizenship and protecting stakeholders. It guides legal and ethical behavior.

Does this help explain the key points of the Tata Code of Conduct in simple terms? Let me know if you need any clarification.

3/11/24, 11:12â€¯AM - Krish: import javax.servlet.ServletException;
import javax.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.io.PrintWriter;

@WebServlet("/LoginServlet")
public class LoginServlet extends HttpServlet {

    // Dummy user credentials for demonstration purposes
    private static final String VALID_USERNAME = "admin";
    private static final String VALID_PASSWORD = "password";

    protected void doPost(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) throws ServletException, IOException {
        String username = request.getParameter("username");
        String password = request.getParameter("password");

        PrintWriter out = response.getWriter();

        if (VALID_USERNAME.equals(username) && VALID_PASSWORD.equals(password)) {
            out.println("<html><body>");
            out.println("<h2>Login Successful</h2>");
            out.println("</body></html>");
        } else {
            out.println("<html><body>");
            out.println("<h2>Invalid Username or Password</h2>");
            out.println("</body></html>");
        }
    }
}
3/11/24, 11:12â€¯AM - Krish: <!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Login Page</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Login</h2>
        <form action="LoginServlet" method="post">
            <label for="username"><b>Username</b></label>
            <input type="text" placeholder="Enter Username" name="username" required>

            <label for="password"><b>Password</b></label>
            <input type="password" placeholder="Enter Password" name="password" required>

            <button type="submit">Login</button>
        </form>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

3/19/24, 1:55â€¯PM - Suzal Kachhadiya: import java.sql.*;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class JDBC_MySQL_SELECT {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Connection cn = null;
        Statement sc = null;
        Scanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);
        
        try {
            Class.forName("com.mysql.jdbc.Driver");
            cn = DriverManager.getConnection("jdbc:mysql://localhost/ajp", "root", "");
            System.out.println("Connection Successful!");
            sc = cn.createStatement();

            String username = scan.nextLine();
            int roll = scan.nextInt();

            String sql = "SELECT * FROM MY_table WHERE StudName='"+username+"' AND Roll='"+roll+"'";
            ResultSet result = sc.executeQuery(sql);
            
            System.out.println("Displaying the content of the table:\n");

            if(result.next()){
                System.out.println("verified.");
            } else{
                System.out.println("not verified.");
            }

            result.close();
            sc.close();
            cn.close();
            
        } catch (ClassNotFoundException e) {
            System.out.println("Exception:"+e.getMessage());
        } catch (SQLException e) {
            System.out.println("Exception:"+e.getMessage());
        }
    }
}

<!DOCTYPE html>

	<form action="loginForm" method="post">
		Email: <input type="text" name="email1" /> <br/> <br/>

4/24/24, 11:11â€¯AM - Harshil: package in.sp.backend;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.io.PrintWriter;
import java.sql.Connection;
import java.sql.DriverManager;
import java.sql.PreparedStatement;
import java.sql.ResultSet;

import javax.servlet.RequestDispatcher;
import javax.servlet.ServletException; 
import javax.servlet.annotation.WebServlet; 
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet; 
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest; 
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpSession;


@WebServlet("/loginForm")
public class Login extends HttpServlet
{
	@Override
	protected void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp) throws ServletException, IOException
	{
		PrintWriter out= resp.getWriter();
		String myemail=req.getParameter("email1");
		String mypass = req.getParameter("pass1");
		try
		{
			Class.forName("com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver");
			Connection con = DriverManager.getConnection("jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/user","root","harshil@*18*");
			
			PreparedStatement ps = con.prepareStatement(" select * from register where email=? and password=?");

			ps.setString(1, myemail); 
			ps.setString(2, mypass);
			ResultSet rs = ps.executeQuery(); 
			if(rs.next())
			{
				HttpSession session= req.getSession();
				session.setAttribute("session_name",rs.getString("name"));
				
				RequestDispatcher rd = req.getRequestDispatcher("/profile.jsp"); 
				rd.include(req, resp);
			}
			
			else
			{
				resp.setContentType("text/html");
				out.print("<h3 style color:red> Email id and Password didn't matched!! </h3>");
				RequestDispatcher rd = req.getRequestDispatcher("/login.jsp"); 
				rd.include(req, resp);
			}
		}
		catch(Exception e)
		{
			e.printStackTrace();
			
			resp.setContentType("text/html");
			out.print("<h3 style='color:red'> "+e.getMessage()+" </h3>");
			RequestDispatcher rd = req.getRequestDispatcher("/login.jsp"); 
			rd.include(req, resp);
		}
		
	}
	
}

*àª¤à«àª¯àª¾àª° àª¬àª¾àª¦ àª¬à«‡ àª•à«‡ àª¤à«àª°àª£ àª˜àªŸàª¨àª¾àª“àª¨àª¾ àª•àª¾àª°àª£à«‡ àª­àª¾àª°àª¤à«€àª¯ àª…àª°à«àª¥àª¤àª‚àª¤à«àª° àªàª•àª¦àª® àªªàª¡à«€ àª­àª¾àª—à«àª¯à« àª¹àª¤à«.! àª¤à«‡àª®àª£à«‡ àª¸à«‹àª¨à« àª—à«€àª°àªµà«‡ àª®à«àª•àªµàª¾àª¨à«€ àªµàª¾àª¤ àªªàª¡àª¤à«€ àª®à«‚àª•à«€, àª•àª¾àª°àª£ àª•à«‡ àª¤à«‡àª¨àª¾àª¥à«€ àª­àª¾àª°àª¤àª¨à«€ àª†àª¬àª°à«‚ àª†àª‚àª¤àª°àª°àª¾àª·à«àªŸà«àª°à«€àª¯ àª°à«€àª¤à«‡ àª¬à«€àª²àª•à«àª² àª§à«‹àªµàª¾àªˆ àª°àª¹à«€ àª¹àª¤à«€,  àª…àª¨à«‡ àªœàª¨àª¤àª¾àª¨à«‹ àª°à«‹àª· àªªàª£ àª¸àª¾àª¤àª®àª¾ àª†àª¸àª®àª¾àª¨à«‡ àª¹àª¤à«‹.!

5/22/24, 9:06â€¯AM - Kenil Kanani: <?php
// Database Configuration (Replace placeholders with your actual values)
$servername = "your_servername"; // Usually 'localhost'
$username = "your_username";
$password = "your_password";
$dbname = "my_data"; // Your database name

// Create connection
$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

// Check connection
if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
}

// CRUD Operations (Example usage)

// CREATE (Insert new text)
if (isset($_POST['new_text'])) {
    $newText = $_POST['new_text'];
    $wordCount = str_word_count($newText);
    $sql = "INSERT INTO texts (content, word_count) VALUES ('$newText', $wordCount)";
    $conn->query($sql);
}

// READ (Fetch all texts)
$sql = "SELECT * FROM texts";
$result = $conn->query($sql);

if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
    while($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
        echo "ID: " . $row["id"]. " - Content: " . $row["content"]. " - Word Count: " . $row["word_count"]. "<br>";
    }
} else {
    echo "No texts found.";
}

// UPDATE (Update an existing text by ID)
if (isset($_POST['update_id'], $_POST['updated_text'])) {
    $updateId = $_POST['update_id'];
    $updatedText = $_POST['updated_text'];
    $updatedWordCount = str_word_count($updatedText);
    $sql = "UPDATE texts SET content='$updatedText', word_count=$updatedWordCount WHERE id=$updateId";
    $conn->query($sql);
}

// DELETE (Delete a text by ID)
if (isset($_POST['delete_id'])) {
    $deleteId = $_POST['delete_id'];
    $sql = "DELETE FROM texts WHERE id=$deleteId";
    $conn->query($sql);
}

$conn->close(); // Close the database connection
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>Add New Text</h2>
<form method="post">
  <textarea name="new_text" rows="4" cols="50"></textarea><br>
  <input type="submit" value="Add">
</form>

<h2>Update Text</h2>
<form method="post">
  ID to Update: <input type="number" name="update_id"><br>
  New Text: <textarea name="updated_text" rows="4" cols="50"></textarea><br>
  <input type="submit" value="Update">
</form>

<h2>Delete Text</h2>
<form method="post">
  ID to Delete: <input type="number" name="delete_id"><br>
  <input type="submit" value="Delete">
</form>

</body>
</html>

                $_SESSION['name'] = "Kenil";
                $_SESSION['exp'] = time()+10;
                ?>
            window.location.href = "profile.php";
        }
    </script>
